The Anatomy of Active Attacks in the USA, 2000-2023

Below are a number of visualizations that help illustrate the characteristics of active attacks included in the dataset.

Attack Frequency

The graphic below represents the frequency of active attacks from 2000 to 2023. There appears to be more events in the last five years (mean = 47) than the first five years (mean = 8.5) or second five years (mean = 16.6); however, this may be an artifact of media coverage. Events that occurred during the first part of this data collection period likely did not get the national coverage that they do now. Furthermore, technology and search engines have improved dramatically over the 24 years of this data collection period.

Time of Day

The bulk of attacks happen between the hours of 7:00 am and 4:00 pm (57.46%). However, as the below graphic shows, attacks occur at all times of the day.
